# Per-event SVG badges overlaid on LabwareCanvas

## Context

Spec-021 added tri-state preview control in the sidebar. This spec
extends the tri-state UX to the canvas itself — the user sees proposed
events as ghost wells AND as small interactive badges floating over
those wells, with accept/reject/pending buttons directly accessible
without leaving the canvas.

The ghost wells already render (`previewWellContents` via
`LabwareCanvas.tsx` and `DualLabwarePane.tsx`). This spec adds the
badges as a new overlay layer in the same SVG.

**Why pure SVG (not `<foreignObject>`):** the canvas is SVG end-to-end
today and `<foreignObject>` introduces z-index and accessibility
quirks. SVG-native buttons are more consistent.

## Requirements

### 1. Geometry helper

**Read `LabwareCanvas.tsx` (~880 lines)** to understand how wells are
positioned in SVG coordinates. There is likely a function that maps a
well ID to an (x, y) center coordinate. Export it (or a new helper) so
`PreviewEventBadges` can compute badge positions without duplicating
geometry logic.

If the geometry is inline and can't easily be extracted, create a new
helper function `wellCenterSvg(labware, wellId): { cx: number; cy: number }`
in `app/src/graph/lib/labwareView.ts` (or wherever the existing view
helpers live) that mirrors the LabwareCanvas positioning logic. Reuse
the existing constants for well pitch, plate padding, etc.

### 2. PreviewEventBadges component

Create `app/src/graph/labware/PreviewEventBadges.tsx`:

```tsx
import type { PlateEvent } from '../../types/event';
import type { Labware } from '../../types/labware';
import { getAffectedWells } from '../../types/events';

interface Props {
  labware: Labware;
  previewEvents: PlateEvent[];
  previewEventStates: Map<string, 'pending' | 'accepted' | 'rejected'>;
  onSetState: (eventId: string, state: 'pending' | 'accepted' | 'rejected') => void;
  onHoverEvent?: (eventId: string | null) => void;
  wellCenter: (wellId: string) => { cx: number; cy: number };
}

const BADGE_RADIUS = 9;
const BADGE_SPACING = 14;
const STATE_COLOR: Record<'pending' | 'accepted' | 'rejected', { stroke: string; fill: string }> = {
  pending:  { stroke: '#be4bdb', fill: '#fff' },
  accepted: { stroke: '#2f9e44', fill: '#d3f9d8' },
  rejected: { stroke: '#868e96', fill: '#f1f3f5' },
};

export function PreviewEventBadges({
  labware,
  previewEvents,
  previewEventStates,
  onSetState,
  onHoverEvent,
  wellCenter,
}: Props) {
  // Filter to events that touch at least one well of THIS labware
  const eventsForLabware = previewEvents.filter((event) => {
    const eventLabwareId = (event.details as any)?.labwareId;
    // Include if labwareId matches, OR (transfer) source/dest matches
    // Actually — we only need to compute wells here because the
    // DualLabwarePane parent has already filtered by labware. But do a
    // defensive filter to be safe.
    return eventLabwareId === labware.labwareId
      || (event.details as any)?.source?.labwareInstanceId === labware.labwareId
      || (event.details as any)?.target?.labwareInstanceId === labware.labwareId
      || (event.details as any)?.source_labwareId === labware.labwareId
      || (event.details as any)?.dest_labwareId === labware.labwareId;
  });

  // Compute badge positions, grouping by well centroid so same-well events stack
  const positioned = eventsForLabware.map((event) => {
    const wells = getAffectedWells(event).filter(Boolean);
    if (wells.length === 0) return null;
    // Centroid = average of well centers
    const centers = wells.map((w) => wellCenter(w));
    const cx = centers.reduce((s, c) => s + c.cx, 0) / centers.length;
    // Topmost = min y
    const topY = Math.min(...centers.map((c) => c.cy));
    return { event, cx, cy: topY - BADGE_SPACING };
  }).filter((e): e is NonNullable<typeof e> => e !== null);

  // Stack badges that share near-identical centroids
  const stacked: Array<{ event: PlateEvent; cx: number; cy: number }> = [];
  for (const entry of positioned) {
    const collisions = stacked.filter(
      (s) => Math.abs(s.cx - entry.cx) < 4 && Math.abs(s.cy - entry.cy) < 4,
    );
    stacked.push({ ...entry, cy: entry.cy - collisions.length * BADGE_SPACING });
  }

  return (
    <g className="preview-event-badges">
      {stacked.map(({ event, cx, cy }) => {
        const state = previewEventStates.get(event.eventId) ?? 'pending';
        const color = STATE_COLOR[state];
        return (
          <g
            key={event.eventId}
            transform={`translate(${cx}, ${cy})`}
            onMouseEnter={() => onHoverEvent?.(event.eventId)}
            onMouseLeave={() => onHoverEvent?.(null)}
            style={{ cursor: 'pointer' }}
          >
            {/* background pill */}
            <rect
              x={-3 * BADGE_RADIUS}
              y={-BADGE_RADIUS}
              width={6 * BADGE_RADIUS}
              height={2 * BADGE_RADIUS}
              rx={BADGE_RADIUS}
              fill={color.fill}
              stroke={color.stroke}
              strokeWidth={1.5}
              opacity={state === 'rejected' ? 0.5 : 1}
            />
            {/* Accept ✓ */}
            <g
              transform={`translate(${-2 * BADGE_RADIUS}, 0)`}
              onClick={(e) => { e.stopPropagation(); onSetState(event.eventId, 'accepted'); }}
              style={{ pointerEvents: 'all' }}
            >
              <circle r={BADGE_RADIUS - 2} fill="transparent" />
              <text textAnchor="middle" dominantBaseline="central" fontSize="11" fill={state === 'accepted' ? '#2f9e44' : '#868e96'}>✓</text>
            </g>
            {/* Pending ○ */}
            <g
              transform="translate(0, 0)"
              onClick={(e) => { e.stopPropagation(); onSetState(event.eventId, 'pending'); }}
              style={{ pointerEvents: 'all' }}
            >
              <circle r={BADGE_RADIUS - 2} fill="transparent" />
              <text textAnchor="middle" dominantBaseline="central" fontSize="11" fill={state === 'pending' ? '#be4bdb' : '#868e96'}>○</text>
            </g>
            {/* Reject ✗ */}
            <g
              transform={`translate(${2 * BADGE_RADIUS}, 0)`}
              onClick={(e) => { e.stopPropagation(); onSetState(event.eventId, 'rejected'); }}
              style={{ pointerEvents: 'all' }}
            >
              <circle r={BADGE_RADIUS - 2} fill="transparent" />
              <text textAnchor="middle" dominantBaseline="central" fontSize="11" fill={state === 'rejected' ? '#c92a2a' : '#868e96'}>✗</text>
            </g>
          </g>
        );
      })}
    </g>
  );
}
```

Adjust geometry constants to match the existing LabwareCanvas scale
conventions. If wells are rendered at roughly 20-30px radius, adjust
BADGE_RADIUS accordingly.

### 3. LabwareCanvas integration

Add an optional `previewEventBadges?: ReactNode` prop to
`LabwareCanvas.tsx`. Render it inside the main SVG after the wells are
drawn but before any selection/highlight overlays. This is purely
additive — existing behavior unchanged when the prop is not passed.

### 4. DualLabwarePane wiring

In `DualLabwarePane.tsx`, for each pane compute:
- The labware currently focused in that pane (already done)
- The filtered previewEvents that touch that labware (already done —
  the spec-021 filter now excludes rejected events FROM THE GHOST WELLS,
