### 5. Hover highlighting

When the user hovers a badge, the corresponding ghost wells should be
emphasized. DualLabwarePane or LabwareCanvas already has a concept of
highlighted wells — reuse that via the `onHoverEvent` callback on
PreviewEventBadges:

```ts
const [hoveredPreviewEventId, setHoveredPreviewEventId] = useState<string | null>(null);
const hoverHighlightedWells = useMemo(() => {
  if (!hoveredPreviewEventId) return new Set<string>();
  const event = previewEvents.find((e) => e.eventId === hoveredPreviewEventId);
  if (!event) return new Set<string>();
  return new Set(getAffectedWells(event));
}, [hoveredPreviewEventId, previewEvents]);
```

Pass `hoverHighlightedWells` into the existing highlightedWells prop of
LabwareCanvas, merging with any pre-existing highlights. This is the
minimum viable highlight — polish styling in a follow-up.

